Feature: WFS Export

    Scenario: Opening Management Tab
         Given I am on Hootenanny
         And I click Get Started
         When I select the "sprocket" div

    Scenario: I can add export the DC GIS data as WFS
         When I click on the "Datasets" option in the "settingsSidebar"
         When I click the "AllDataTypesACucumber" Dataset
         And I context click the "AllDataTypesACucumber" Dataset
         And I click the "Export" context menu item
         Then I should see element "[id='fileExportOutputName']" with value "AllDataTypesACucumber"
         When I select the "Web Feature Service (WFS)" option in the "File Geodatabase" combobox
         And I press "big.loud" span with text "Export"
         And I wait 30 "seconds" to see "label" element with text "WFS Resources Url"
         Then I open the wfs export url

    Scenario: Opening Management Tab
         Given I am on Hootenanny
         And I click Get Started
         When I select the "sprocket" div

    Scenario: I can delete the WFS export
         When I click on the "WFS Exports" option in the "settingsSidebar"
         Then I should see an element "span.hoverDiv2"
         When I click on the "up" button in the "wfsdatasettable"
         Then I should see an element "input.wfsfileExportOutputName"
         Then I select the "x" div
         When I click on the "trash" button in the "wfsdatasettable"
         And I accept the alert
         And I wait 3 seconds
         Then I should not see an element "button.up"
